# .gitignore for Terraform
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Some Terraform files must NEVER be committed: state (can contain secrets and
# is environment-specific) and any tfvars holding sensitive input.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Provider plugins & local working files downloaded by `terraform init`
**/.terraform/*

# State files — the source of truth mapping config to real objects.
# Can contain secrets; belongs in a remote backend, never in git.
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*

# Crash logs
crash.log
crash.*.log

# Variable files — may contain tenant IDs / secrets.
# Ignore all *.tfvars EXCEPT the shareable *.example template.
*.tfvars
*.tfvars.json
!*.tfvars.example

# CLI config that can hold credentials
*.tfrc
.terraformrc

# NOTE: .terraform.lock.hcl is deliberately NOT ignored.
# That lock file pins exact provider versions/hashes and SHOULD be committed
# so everyone on the team resolves identical providers.
